  "543": {
    "p": "It was an ancient style of compliment to give a larger portion of food to the conqueror, or person to whom respect was to be shown. See Virg. Æn. viii. 181. Thus Benjamin was honoured with a \"double portion.\" Gen. xliii. 34.",
